data.enText: a way of entering or reaching a place

data.chText: 去那农舍的唯一通路是穿过田野。
data.enText: The only access to the farmhouse is across the fields.

data.chText: 欢迎残疾人士参观，坐轮椅可以方便地到达多数设施。
data.enText: Disabled visitors are welcome; there is good wheelchair access to most facilities.

data.chText: 警察从一扇破窗户里钻了进去。
data.enText: The police gained access through a broken window.
the opportunity or right to use sth or to see sb/sth

data.chText: 学生必须有机会使用好的资源。
data.enText: Students must have access to good resources.

data.chText: 使用这个计算机系统需要口令。
data.enText: You need a password to get access to the computer system.

data.chText: 记者被挡住，无法见到总统。
data.enText: Journalists were denied access to the President.

data.chText: 很多离婚父亲只有在周末才有权见到自己的孩子。
data.enText: Many divorced fathers only have access to their children at weekends (= they are allowed by law to see them only at weekends) .
to open a computer file in order to get or add information
to reach, enter or use sth
The loft can be accessed by a ladder.

simple_means.memory_skill: ac 加强 + cess 行走，前进 → 一再向前走 → 接近

ex.chText: 我们在入口处排队参观展览。
ex.enText: We queued up at the entrance for the exhibition.

synonyms.bx: 含义广泛，作“进入”解时，尤指以被人们注意到的方式；作“入口”解时，一般指有门或围栏的入口处。

ex.chText: 大楼唯一的入口被堵住了。
ex.enText: The only access to the building was blocked.
Access to the restrooms is through the hall.

synonyms.bx: 指进入建筑物或到达某处的通道，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 我会在游乐园入口处等你。
ex.enText: I'll wait for you at the entry to the amusement park.

ex.chText: 我们可以把伞放在入口处。
ex.enText: We can leave our umbrellas at the entry.

ex.chText: 洞穴的入口被树丛遮掩着。
ex.enText: The entry to the cave was hidden by trees.

ex.chText: 在博物馆的入口处发现了一枚炸弹。
ex.enText: A bomb was found at the entry to the museum.

synonyms.bx: 指某一场所（如建筑物、大厅等）的入口处或进入的通道。

tr: the act of approaching or entering
example: he gained access to the building

tr: a way of entering or leaving
example: he took a wrong turn on the access to the bridge

tr: (computer science) the operation of reading or writing stored information
the right to obtain or make use of or take advantage of something (as services or membership)
a code (a series of characters or digits) that must be entered in some way (typed or dialed or spoken) to get the use of something (a telephone line or a computer or a local area network etc.)

example: How does one access the attic in this house?
I cannot get to the T.V. antenna, even if I climb on the roof

tr: obtain or retrieve from a storage device
as of information on a computer

value.def: If you have access to a building or other place, you are able or allowed to go into it.

example.ex: The facilities have been adapted to give access to wheelchair users.
example.tran: 这些设施已经改造过以方便轮椅使用者进入。

example.ex: Scientists have only recently been able to gain access to the area...
example.tran: 科学家直到最近才得以进入该地区。

example.ex: The Mortimer Hotel offers easy access to central London.
example.tran: 从莫蒂默旅馆去往伦敦市中心交通近便。

value.def: If you have access to something such as information or equipment, you have the opportunity or right to see it or use it.

example.ex: ...a Code of Practice that would give patients right of access to their medical records.
example.tran: 允许病人查看自己病历的职业准则

example.ex: ...whether one has access to a dish and the other accoutrements needed to watch satellite TV.
example.tran: 是否能使用碟型卫星天线以及其他观看卫星电视所需要的装备

value.tran: 查阅（或使用）的机会（或权利）

value.def: If you have access to a person, you have the opportunity or right to see them or meet them.

example.ex: He was not allowed access to a lawyer.
My ex-wife deliberately sabotages my access to the children.
example.tran: 我的前妻蓄意阻挠我见孩子。

value.tran: 接近（或面见）的机会（或权利）

value.def: If you access something, especially information held on a computer, you succeed in finding or obtaining it.

example.ex: You've illegally accessed and misused confidential security files.
example.tran: 你已经非法访问并盗用了机密的安全文件。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to go, to proceed 行走, 前进
rootsaffixes.title: ced, ceed, cess

partsOfSpeech.dec: ac 加强 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 一起走 → 同意
ac 加强 + cess 行走，前进 → 一再向前走 → 接近
an 加强 + cest〔= cess〕行走，前进 + or 表人 → 走了很久的人 → 祖先
ante 前面 + ced 行走，前进 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 先行的；以前的
ced 行走，前进 + e →〔使〕走开 → 割让
ex 出 + ceed 行走，前进 → 走出去 → 超越
inter 在…之间 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 在两者中间走 → 调停
pre 预先 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 在先，优于
pre 前；预先 + ced 行走，前进 + ent 表名词 → 在前面的东西 → 先例
pro 在前 + ced 行走，前进 + ure 表结果 → 前面经过的〔历程〕→ 程序
pro 向前 + ceed 行走，前进 → 继续进行，前进
pro 向前 + cess 行走，前进 → 向前走的〔历程〕→ 过程
process 过程；进行 + ion 表名词 → 向前走 → 队伍
re 向后 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 后退
re 回 + cess 行走，前进 → 走回去 → 休息
recess 休息；暂停 + ion 表动作 → 走回去 → 撤退
se 分开 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 分开走 → 脱离
suc 下 + ceed 行走，前进 → 从下面走到上面 → 成功
suc 下 + cess 行走，前进 → 成功，胜利
un 无 + precedent 前例 + ed 表形容词 → 史无前例的
